        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 9:40AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 939 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bradshaw, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Bradshaw around 945 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Lake Abilene, Drasco,
Camp Tonkawa, Pumphrey, and Ovalo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
